# Brain cron configuration — the brain's scheduled tasks.
# Standard 5-field cron schedule + command, one per line; imported into the brain
# user's crontab in the distro. Empty by default. Commands run in-distro as the brain.
#
#   minute  hour  day-of-month  month  day-of-week   command
#
# Re-import after editing to apply.


## NEURON CRON ENTRIES
# Ingestion/consumption pipeline schedules. Commands call neuron scripts under
# /opt/input_neurons (the neuron code, mapped from <brain>/input_neurons).
#
# Example — hourly keep-current reindex:
# 0 * * * * /opt/input_neurons/run.sh reindex >> ~/logs/neuron/cron.log 2>&1


## BRAIN_FUNCTION CRON ENTRIES
# General brain-management schedules. Commands call scripts in the in-distro script
# seam at /opt/brain_wsl_in_distro_scripts.
#
# Example — nightly maintenance task:
# 30 3 * * * bash /opt/brain_wsl_in_distro_scripts/some_task.sh >> ~/logs/brain/cron.log 2>&1
